{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id6bf062a3-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1328"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1328"},"text":"§ 1328.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Aquaculture","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id6bf062a4-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1328/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Authority to permit discharge of specific pollutants","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Administrator is authorized, after public hearings, to permit the discharge of a specific pollutant or pollutants under controlled conditions associated with an approved aquaculture project under Federal or State supervision pursuant to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s1342"},"text":"section 1342 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id6bf062a5-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1328/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Procedures and guidelines","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Administrator shall by regulation establish any procedures and guidelines which the Administrator deems necessary to carry out this section. Such regulations shall require the application to such discharge of each criterion, factor, procedure, and requirement applicable to a permit issued under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s1342"},"text":"section 1342 of this title","children":[],"tail":", as the Administrator determines necessary to carry out the objective of this chapter."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id6bf062a6-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s1328/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" State administration","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Each State desiring to administer its own permit program within its jurisdiction for discharge of a specific pollutant or pollutants under controlled conditions associated with an approved aquaculture project may do so if upon submission of such program the Administrator determines such program is adequate to carry out the objective of this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id6bf062a7-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-30/ch758"},"text":"June 30, 1948, ch. 758","children":[],"tail":", title III, § 318, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/500/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–500, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1972-10-18"},"text":"Oct. 18, 1972","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/86/877"},"text":"86 Stat. 877","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/217/s63"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–217, § 63","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1977-12-27"},"text":"Dec. 27, 1977","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/91/1599"},"text":"91 Stat. 1599","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id6bf062a8-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id6bf062a9-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id6bf062aa-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1977—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/217"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–217","children":[],"tail":" inserted “pursuant to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s1342"},"text":"section 1342 of this title","children":[],"tail":"” after “Federal or State supervision”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/217"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–217","children":[],"tail":" struck out “, not later than "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 1974","children":[],"tail":",” after “The Administrator shall by regulation” in existing provisions and inserted provisions that the regulations require the application to the discharge of each criterion, factor, procedure, and requirement applicable to a permit issued under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s1342"},"text":"section 1342 of this title","children":[],"tail":", as the Administrator determines necessary to carry out the objectives of this chapter."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/217"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–217","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (c)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
